rComments: Very understanding, caring prof. Fair marker and doesn't surprise you. 100% would recommend him
Fun lectures. Going to class recommended. Really goes into detail in lectures. Slides are a bit hard to follow, though.  The Irish accent is another reason to go to his lectures.

Found his lectures to be very interesting and thorough. He taught the material very well and added in lots of modern day references. If you go to class regularly and pay attention you will do very well! The readings supplied are only necessary for reference.
Good prof! Looks like Hugh Jackman

I loved the course and the teacher! He is quite funny and is passionate about classical sociological theories. He is very easy to understand and clear with what he expects. Going to class is a must, reading the papers is recommended but not a must. I would suggest you take any of his courses, he'll make you work for your grade but totally worth it!

The classical sociological theories class is so boring, but professor Flynn tries really hard to make it suck less. He is enthusiastic and funny, and tries really hard to  include videos/interesting materials in the course in order to make it more bearable. Doing the readings and going through powerpoints guarantees you an A!
lectures were engaging - sometimes his slides were a little hard to understand but for the most part they were clear  he's a super nice guy plus the irish accent made the class 10 times better

Very fair teacher, always there to help or just discuss your opinion on the readings. No textbook but you have to do the assigned readings because they can be difficult and he goes over them in class. The exams are based on your level of understanding rather than memorization. It was cool considering it can be a very dull subject. Awesome teacher.
Honestly just avoid this prof and the course, you'll be way better off.

Lots of reading. Doesnt use a textbook to give students a break, and instead provides you with all the readings you need. Exams are super fair and if you keep up with reading you'll be laughing. Great prof.
He is an amazing prof! If you don't miss lectures and do the readings, you will get a good mark! He is very clear on what he wants from his students!

One of the most amazing profs I've had so far. Extremely clear on what he wants from his assignments, organized, fair marker, and gives options for essay topics. Posts on BB! Only class I did readings for because I actually respected and cared about his class, though readings are mandatory. His Irish accents makes things so much more enjoyable too!

His rubric is atrocious and his lecture slides are impossible to study from. First midterm was easy but final really screwed a lot of people. I'm not interested in playing the guessing game. Just give me a clear marking schemeguideline and I'll give you what you want. If you're into having a lot of stress and impossible tasks to do, take thisclass

I absolutely loved this prof! He is funny and although the course can be very boring at times, he tries to make it fun and engaging. The workload is pretty average, and the midterm and final are super straight forward, if you listen and do your readings, you'd know exactly what to expect.

Prof Flynn is a pretty good guy. His powerpoint slides are riddled with spellinggrammatical errors, but he's smart, and not a bad lecturer. His midterm was insanely easy and I got a perfect mark. Easy A+ if you just learn and memorize the material he gives you.
Pretty easy class if you read the textbook and study what he says to focus on. Got perfect on the midterm, and the papers were both A+ marks. Know your stuff and write it clearly. Easy A+

meh he was an ok prof. kinda awkward in my opinion, but his lectures aren't bad. his marking scheme is very vague so make sure u ask him on stuff ur confused about. also him and his TAs r annoyingly hard markers, so do ur readings and read the ppts and u should be fine. he encourages class discussion, so don't be afraid to speak up in class
He's a great prof! He's somewhat of a tough marker but if you go to him and ask him for help... he's more than willing to help you and make you understand. Very easy to talk to :)
Great prof. however he marks ridiculous hard.
midterm was very specific. prof was funny and interesting but wouldn't recommend it for an elective.

I liked the way he explained things in class, it helped put things in a better perspectives. The videos and images he's shown in class were helpful too. No textbook, puts the slides online, but they are not enough. You HAVE to do the readings in order to fully grasp the content. If you only rely on the slides, you might do pretty bad.

I was expecting to not enjoy this class because of the dry material, however Professor Flynn made it one of my favourite classes! He was funny, created group conversation, and I was very impressed by how I could go in to class not understanding the reading at all and leave with complete understanding. My advice is to definitely take his classes.

A pretty dry subject but he made it decent. He's very easy to listen to especially with his accent, and he's pretty funny. I don't agree that he pushes his views on people, in fact he's very open to discussion. If you have to take this class I'd take it with professor Flynn.

Lectures were interesting most of the time, especially because this prof likes discussion.  The midterm was very hard and the short answers were very specific.  The final was still pretty tough, but not as bad as the midterm.  He gave us all a chance to boost our marks buy assigning a really simple and interesting essay.  Not sure if I'd recommend.

Here's what you need to know: - Lectures are easy to understand, and posted before class - Midterm is confusing  - Essay is easy, especially if you do the media topic - Loves to talk about gender, sexuality, media - Class debates break out, which are awesome - Irish, and hilarious - Shows the best YouTube videos

An amazing prof! he manages to make a three hour class not as bad because he gets people talking and engaged a lot throughout the class! His accent is amazing to listen to and he uses a lot of pop culture references to make the theories more relevant. his midterm is tough if you dont read the textbook! Definitely worth the 3hour lecture!

I think this prof is very stimulating. The three hour Monday night lectures that I attended weren't too bad. The prof's Irish accent seemed to help my attentiveness and my study habits as I would read my notes with an Irish accent. Great guy, funny comments. The class consists of constant open debating and discussion which keeps the class awake.
Hard to study for the exams because it is not what is taught in class

everything on the exam is straight out off of the powerpoints and textbook readings. And all of his powerpoints are filled with info (which is super helpful). He was a great marker, but his TA's were a little tough. There are 4 exams (2 midterms, 2 finals) and one assignement. But as long as you read, you're good.
This Prof pushes his own views very hard. You will excel if you write your exams and papers under the pretext of the Prof's views, however if you dare to express your own views be ready to fail.

Awesome teacher! He took over part way through and managed to keep the class engaged and to carry us through until the end. Lectures are interesting and easy to follow. He is clear and very helpful both in person and through email. Respectful, approachable and non-confrontational. Easily accepts students opinions and encourages class participation
